The paper discusses techniques to tackle algorithmic fairness problems in deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Given that the paper focuses on deep learning models, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses the importance of interpretability, which is relevant to cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning in decision making applications, which is relevant to computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
